The paper presents a modification of the superposition calculus that is related to abductive reasoning, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the correctness and completeness of the calculus, which is a topic in logic and set theory (cs.LO). Additionally, the paper proposes a procedure that generates explanations that should be useful to a human user, which is related to programming languages and compilers (cs.PL) and natural language processing (cs.CL). Finally, the paper discusses several extensions to the approach, which is related to software engineering (cs.SE).
